Trump and U.K. Prime Minister Starmer discuss tariffs, Ukraine President Donald Trump hosted a meeting at the White House with British Prime Minister Keir Starmer at the White House on Thursday followed by a joint news conference. Trump told reporters that Starmer had “earned whatever they pay him” in working to convince Trump not to place tariffs on the United Kingdom, and suggested he may not do so. Starmer is the latest European leader — French President Emmanuel Macron visited earlier this week — expected to plead with Trump not to abandon Ukraine as he seeks to end the war. Trump also said Thursday that he plans to visit the United Kingdom in “the near future.”
